ong)|Footprints in the Sand]]\" <br> [[Argentine Tango]] & [[Cha-cha-cha (dance)|Cha-cha-cha]] Fusion / \"All the Way\"\n|10<br>10<br>10\n|10<br>10<br>10\n|10<br>10<br>10\n! style=\"background:gold;\" |Winner\n|}\n{{clear}}\n<sup>1</sup> Score by guest judge [[Alfonso Ribeiro]].\n\n<sup>2</sup> This week only, for \"Partner Switch-Up\" week, Irwin performed with [[Valentin Chmerkovskiy]] instead of Hough. Hough performed with [[Alexa PenaVega]].\n\n<sup>3</sup> Score given by guest judge [[Maksim Chmerkovskiy]].\n\n<sup>4</sup> Score given by guest judge [[Olivia Newton-John]].\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n\n===ARIA Music Awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Nominated works\n! Award\n! Result\n! Lost to\n|-\n|[[ARIA Music Awards of 2007|2007]]\n|''Bindi Kid Fitness with Steve Irwin and The Crocmen''\n|rowspan=\"2\" |[[ARIA Award for Best Children's Album|Best Children's Album]]\n|{{nominated}}\n|[[The Wiggles]] \u2013 ''[[Pop Go the Wiggles!]]''\n|-\n|[[ARIA Music Awards of 2009|2009]]\n|''Bindi Kid Fitness 2 Jungle Dance Party''\n|{{nominated}}\n|[[The Wiggles]] \u2013 ''[[Go Bananas! (album)|Go Bananas!]]''\n|-\n|}\n\n===Logie Awards===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! colspan=\"2\"| Nominated works\n! Award\n! Result\n! Lost to\n|-\n|[[Logie Awards of 2008|2008]]\n|Bindi Irwin\n|''[[Bindi the Jungle Girl]]''\n|[[Logie Award for Most Popular New Female Talent|Most Popular New Female Talent]]\n|{{won}}\n|{{n/a}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category|Bindi Irwin}}\n* [http://animal.discovery.com/tv/planets-best/terri-bindi/terri-bindi.html Story of Steve and Terri] at [[Animal Planet]]\n* [http://www.australiazoo.com.au Australia Zoo]\n* [http://instagram.com/bindisueirwin Bindi Irwin] on Instagram\n* [https://twitter.com/bindiirwin Bindi Irwin] on Twitter\n* {{IMDb name|id=1134702|name=Bindi Irwin}}\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{s-ach}}\n{{succession box | title=[[Dancing with the Stars (US TV series)|''Dancing with the Stars'' (US)]] winners | before=[[Rumer Willis]] & [[Valentin Chmerkovskiy]]| years=Season 21<br>(Fall 2015 with [[Derek Hough]])|after=[[Nyle DiMarco]] & [[Peta Murgatroyd]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Dancing with the Stars (United States)}}\n{{Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Performer in Children's Programming}}\n{{Steve Irwin}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Irwin, Bindi Sue}}\n[[Category:1998 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Nambour, Queensland]]\n[[Category:People from the Sunshine Coast, Queensland]]\n[[Category:Australian conservationists]]\n[[Category:American conservationists]]\n[[Category:21st-century Australian actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:Australian child actresses]]\n[[Category:American child actresses]]\n[[Category:Actresses from Queensland]]\n[[Category:Australian film actresses]]\n[[Category:Australian television actresses]]\n[[Category:Australian television presenters]]\n[[Category:Australian television personalities]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:American television actresses]]\n[[Category:American television hosts]]\n[[Category:Australian people of American descent]]\n[[Category:Australian people of English descent]]\n[[Category:Australian people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:American people of English descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Irish descent]]\n[[Category:Dancing with the Stars (American TV series) winners]]\n[[Category:Daytime Emmy Award winners]]\n[[Category:Irwin family|Bindi]]\n[[Category:Logie Award winners]]\n[[Category:Participants in American reality television series]]\n[[Category:Children's television presenters]]\n[[Category:Australian children's musicians]]\n[[Category:Australian female singers]]\n[[Category:Australian child singers]]\n[[Category:American children's musicians]]\n[[Category:American female singers]]\n[[Category:American child singers]]\n[[Category:Women television presenters]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Australian television personality and conservationist}} \n{{Use Australian English|date=January 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Bindi Irwin\n| image              = Bindi Irwin in June 2013.jpg\n| caption            = Irwin in June 2013\n| birth_name         = Bindi Sue Irwin\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1998|7|24}}\n| birth_place        = [[Buderim]], [[Queensland]], Australia\n| nationality        = Australian \n| citizenship        = {{plainlist|\n*[[Australian nationality law|Australia]]\n*[[Citizenship of the United States|United States]]}}\n| occupation         = Television personality, conservationist\n| years_active       = 2000\u2013present\n| spouse             = {{marriage|Chandler Powell|2020}}\n| parents            = {{unbulleted list | [[Steve Irwin]] | [[Terri Irwin]]}}\n| relatives          = {{unbulleted list | [[Robert Irwin (television personality)|Robert Irwin]] (brother) | [[Bob Irwin]] (grandfather) }}\n| awards             = {{unbulleted list | [[Logie Award|Silver Logie]] | [[Daytime Emmy Award|Daytime Emmy]]}}\n| website            = \n}}\n'''Bindi Sue Irwin''' (born 24 July 1998)<ref name=\"familybio\">{{cite web | url = http://www.crocodilehunter.com.au/crocodile_hunter/about_steve_terri/family_biography.html |publisher=CrocodileHunter.com | title= The Irwin Family| accessdate=25 March 2001| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20150304014611/http://www.crocodilehunter.com.au/crocodile_hunter/about_steve_terri/family_biography.html | archivedate=4 March 2015| url-status=live}}</ref> is an Australian television personality and conservationist.<ref name=\"cnn250719\">{{cite news |last1=CNN |first1=Lisa Respers France |title=Bindi Irwin gets engaged |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/07/24/entertainment/bindi-irwin-engaged/index.html |date=25 July 2019 |accessdate=25 July 2019 |work=CNN}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Bindi Irwin all grown up, getting married |url=https://7news.com.au/entertainment/bindi-irwin-all-grown-up-getting-married-c-364038 |work=7NEWS.com.au |date=24 July 2019 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.closerweekly.com/posts/bindi-irwin-family-moving-us-98520|title=Are Bindi Irwin and Her Family Moving to the US?|last=Faragalli|first=Samantha|date=22 September 2017|work=[[Closer Weekly]]|access-date=13 October 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171013125608/http://www.closerweekly.com/posts/bindi-irwin-family-moving-us-98520|archivedate=13 October 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref> When she was 9, Irwin hosted ''[[Bindi the Jungle Girl]]'', a children's wildlife documentary TV series. She has also been involved in acting, singing, dancing, rapping, game show hosting, and has created two instructional fitness DVDs. She is also known for winning [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 21)|season 21]] of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'' (US).\n\nBindi Irwin is one of the two children of the late conservationist and television personality [[Steve Irwin]] and his conservationist wife, [[Terri Irwin]], who is currently the owner of the [[Australia Zoo]]. Bindi's younger brother is [[Robert Irwin (television personality)|Robert Irwin]], a television personality and photographer, and she is the granddaughter of naturalist and herpetologist [[Bob Irwin]]. {{As of|2020|March}}, she is married to American professional wakeboarder, Chandler Powell.\n\n==Early life==\nBindi Irwin was born in [[Buderim, Queensland]].<ref name=\"familybio\"/> Her first name comes from the name of her father's favourite female crocodile at the Australia Zoo, and her middle name, Sue, is from the family's late dog Sui, who died in her sleep from cancer on 23 June 2004 at the age of 15. According to her father, ''Bindi'' is an [[Nyungar language]] word that means \"young girl\".<ref name=\"ABCnet\">{{cite web | url=http://www.abc.net.au/children/bindi/interview.htm | title=Bindi: The Jungle Girl | accessdate=1 March 2011 | publisher=ABC.net.au|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140110002740/http://www.abc.net.au/children/bindi/interview.htm|archivedate=10 January 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nShe began appearing on television shows as early as age two.<ref name=CourierMail1>{{cite news|author = Green, Glenis|url = http://www.news.com.au/couriermail/story/0,,20377536-952,00.html|title = Mantle passes to Bindi|work = [[The Courier-Mail]]|date = 9 September 2006|url-status = live|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081222041349/http://www.news.com.au/couriermail/story/0,,20377536-952,00.html|archivedate = 22 December 2008|df = dmy-all}}</ref> She appeared regularly in her father's television shows, including ''[[The Crocodile Hunter Diaries]]'', and in the 2002 film ''[[The Wiggles]]: [[Wiggly Safari]]'' in a credited cast role. She is of [[English people|English]] and [[Irish people|Irish]] ancestry, with abundance of Irish ancestry on her father's side. Bindi stated herself being a dual citizen (Australian-American), in an interview with ''[[Brisbane Times]]'': \"What's really nice is being a dual citizen both here and in the US so I think I get to vote there as well.\"<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/queensland/bindi-irwin-has-big-plans-as-she-marks-her-milestone-birthday-20160723-gqc5qy.html|title=Bindi Irwin has big plans as she marks her milestone birthday|last=Cooper|first=Nathanael|date=23 July 2016|work=[[Brisbane Times]]|access-date=3 March 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170303122505/http://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/queensland/bindi-irwin-has-big-plans-as-she-marks-her-milestone-birthday-20160723-gqc5qy.html|archivedate=3 March 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIrwin was homeschooled until 2014, when she enrolled at [[TAFE Queensland East Coast]]. She has completed a Certificate III in Business, and is currently studying for a Certificate III in Tourism.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Crane|first1=Kris|title=Bindi Irwin looking to take over Australia Zoo and continue Steve Irwin's legacy|url=http://www.couriermail.com.au/news/queensland/bindi-irwin-looking-to-take-over-australia-zoo-and-continue-steve-irwins-legacy/news-story/2dad5f4b27b39af09338f2f8a001e234|accessdate=23 May 2016|work=The Courier Mail|publisher=News Corp|date=23 January 2016|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160825184607/http://www.couriermail.com.au/news/queensland/bindi-irwin-looking-to-take-over-australia-zoo-and-continue-steve-irwins-legacy/news-story/2dad5f4b27b39af09338f2f8a001e234|archivedate=25 August 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref>{{update after|2020|1|30}}\n\n==Career==\nIrwin was the presenter of a 26-part wildlife documentary kids show called ''[[Bindi the Jungle Girl]]'', a production of the [[Discovery Kids]] television network.<ref name=Scotsman1>{{cite web |url =http://living.scotsman.com/index.cfm?id=1307902006|title = I have no fear of losing my life.|author = Cowning, Emma|work= The Scotsman|date = 5 September 2006}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|work = [[Sydney Morning Herald]]|url = http://www.smh.com.au/news/national/bindi-to-fill-her-dads-big-shoes/2006/09/09/1157222376404.html|title = Bindi to fill her dad's big shoes|date = 10 September 2006|url-status = live|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081202065610/http://www.smh.com.au/news/national/bindi-to-fill-her-dads-big-shoes/2006/09/09/1157222376404.html|archivedate = 2 December 2008|df = dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=HeraldSun1>{{cite news |author=Clark, Laine |url=http://www.news.com.au/heraldsun/story/0,,20351375-5005961,00.html |title=Daughter destined to follow in Irwin's footsteps |date=4 September 2006 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071211202334/http://www.news.com.au/heraldsun/story/0%2C%2C20351375-5005961%2C00.html |archivedate=11 December 2007 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Her father was filmed in many of the early shows before his death in September 2006, when production was temporarily put on hold.<ref name=\"Reuters\">{{cite web|url = http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/SYD203498.htm|title = Bindi Irwin Nature Series on Hold for a Year|date = 20 October 2006|publisher = Reuters|url-status = live|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081202042139/http://www.alertnet.org/thenews/newsdesk/SYD203498.htm|archivedate = 2 December 2008|df = dmy-all}}</ref> The series premiered in June 2007 on Discovery Kids.\n\nWhen Bindi was just a year old her grandmother Lyn Irwin died in a car accident on 11 February 2000.<ref>[http://insider.foxnews.com/2016/09/02/letter-steve-irwin-his-parents-has-just-been-discovered A Letter from Steve Irwin to His Parents Has Just Been Discovered <!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117093018/http://insider.foxnews.com/2016/09/02/letter-steve-irwin-his-parents-has-just-been-discovered |date=17 November 2016 }}</ref> Bob has since remarried Judy Irwin.<ref>[http://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/bob-irwin-reveals-sadness-at-losing-contact-with-grandkids-bindi-and-robert/news-story/4ffbcd676fb53ee2467e26def7996d6b Bob Irwin reveals sadness at losing contact with grandkids Bindi and Robert <!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> Bindi's father, Steve, was killed by a [[stingray]] barb on 4 September 2006 when she was eight years old. He was setting up to shoot ocean reef footage for a show that would include segments with himself, because weather prevented him from filming footage for a different show.<ref name=PattayaDailyNews1>\n{{cite web\n|url = http://www.pattayadailynews.com/shownews.php?IDNEWS=0000001387\n|title = Steve Irwin's paid tribute from his family and friends\n|work = Pattaya Daily News\n|date = 23 September 2006\n|author = AJR\n|url-status = dead\n|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081202040026/http://www.pattayadailynews.com/shownews.php?IDNEWS=0000001387\n|archivedate = 2 December 2008\n|df = dmy-all\n}}</ref><ref name=AllHeadlineNews1>\n{{cite web\n|author = Oliveira, Maira\n|url = http://www.allheadlinenews.com/articles/7004870142\n|title = Bindi Irwin To Continue Father's Extraordinary Wildlife Efforts,\n|publisher = AHN Media Corporation\n|date = 15 September 2006\n|url-status = dead\n|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081202021700/http://www.allheadlinenews.com/articles/7004870142\n|archivedate = 2 December 2008\n|df = dmy-all\n}}</ref> Irwin and her mother announced that she would continue her late father's conservation and television work.<ref>[https://www.thisisinsider.com/bindi-irwin-says-shes-always-wanted-to-follow-in-her-dad-steves-footsteps-2018-9 ''Insider'']</ref><ref>[https://www.goodmorningamerica.com/culture/story/crocodile-hunter-steve-irwins-kids-widow-footsteps-57771141 Good Morning America]</ref><ref name=AllHeadlineNews1/> Steve Irwin had said he supported Bindi's career, claiming \"I just want to be co-star to my daughter\".<ref name=\"co-star\">\n{{cite news\n |url         = http://www.news.com.au/couriermail/story/0,23739,20479123-952,00.html\n |title       = Steve knew Bindi would be a star\n |publisher   = Queensland Newspapers\n |date        = 26 May 2006\n |url-status     = live\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20081222033758/http://www.news.com.au/couriermail/story/0,23739,20479123-952,00.html\n |archivedate = 22 December 2008\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 September 2006, Irwin received a standing ovation after delivering a [[eulogy]] for her father in front of a crowd of 5,000 and a worldwide television audience of more than 300 million viewers. In the 2006 ''[[TV Week]]'' readers' poll, her speech received 43 percent of votes and was voted the television moment of the year. Her mother stated that, apart from some assistance with typing, Irwin had written the speech herself.<ref name=\"usatoday.com\"/><ref name=Forbes.com>\n{{cite web\n|author = Passa, Dennis\n|url = https://www.forbes.com/business/manufacturing/feeds/ap/2006/09/19/ap3029795.html\n|title = Irwin Remembered For His 'Zest for Life\".\n|work=Forbes magazine\n|date = 19 September 2006}}</ref><ref name=\"bindispeech\">\n{{cite news\n |title       = My daddy was my hero\n |publisher   = News Limited\n |author      = Chesterton, Ray\n |date        = 20 September 2006\n |url         = http://www.news.com.au/dailytelegraph/story/0,22049,20448393-5009080,00.html\n |accessdate  = 26 May 2007\n |url-status     = live\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20080511155207/http://www.news.com.au/dailytelegraph/story/0,22049,20448393-5009080,00.html\n |archivedate = 11 May 2008\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref><ref name=\"43percent\">\n{{cite news\n |url         = http://www.smh.com.au/news/tv--radio/bindi-tops-tv-poll/2006/12/18/1166290447686.html\n |title       = Bindi tops TV poll\n |work        = Sydney Morning Herald\n |date        = 18 December 2006\n |url-status     = live\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20081202065656/http://www.smh.com.au/news/tv--radio/bindi-tops-tv-poll/2006/12/18/1166290447686.html\n |archivedate = 2 December 2008\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2007, Irwin hosted a US television special about her father called ''My Daddy the Crocodile Hunter''.<ref name=\"PerthNow\">{{cite news|url = http://www.news.com.au/perthnow/story/0,21598,21467635-5005382,00.html|title = Bindi Irwin to make US TV debut|date = 29 March 2007|work = The Sunday Times|first = Peta|last = Hellard|url-status = live|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20081222042208/http://www.news.com.au/perthnow/story/0,21598,21467635-5005382,00.html|archivedate = 22 December 2008|df = dmy-all}}</ref> She also released two child fitness DVDs. Bindi and The Crocmen sang \"Trouble in the Jungle\" on ''[[Today (U.S. TV program)|The Today Show]]'' in November 2007 and Irwin was learning how to play the piano.<ref name=\"usatoday.com\">{{cite news|title = Terri Irwin '20/20' interview transcript excerpts|url = https://www.usatoday.com/life/2006-09-26-terri-irwin-transcript_x.htm|work = USA Today|date = 27 September 2006|url-status = live|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110427085106/http://www.usatoday.com/life/2006-09-26-terri-irwin-transcript_x.htm|archivedate = 27 April 2011|df = dmy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author = Maddison|url = http://people.aol.com/people/article/0,26334,1546416,00.html|title = Steve Irwin's Daughter Bindi Filming Own Show|work = Time|date = 16 October 2006|accessdate = 16 October 2006|url-status = live|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20061108030506/http://people.aol.com/people/article/0,26334,1546416,00.html|archivedate = 8 November 2006|df = dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2006, at age 8, Irwin appeared on the cover of the Australian magazine ''[[New Idea]]'', the youngest person to have done so in the magazine's 104-year history.<ref name=\"SMHBindiStardom\">{{cite news | url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/entertainment/bindi-set-for-stardom/2006/09/26/1159036536136.html | title=Bindi set for stardom | work=Sydney Morning Herald | date=26 September 2006 | accessdate=28 September 2006 | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080523225150/http://www.smh.com.au/news/entertainment/bindi-set-for-stardom/2006/09/26/1159036536136.html | archivedate=23 May 2008 | df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Terri and Bindi Irwin.jpg|thumb]] [[File:Terri and Bindi Irwin 2.jpg|thumb|Photos showing Irwin and her mother [[Terri Irwin|Terri]] at [[Edwards Air Force Base|Edwards AFB]] to film a segment for ''[[Bindi the Jungle Girl]]'' in 2007]]\nIn early January 2007, Irwin appeared on ''[[The Ellen DeGeneres Show]]''. At that time, she was also scheduled for appearances on the ''[[Late Show with David Letterman]]'' and an attendance with [[Russell Crowe]] at a major dinner. She was promoting her new video, ''Bindi Kid Fitness'', and fulfilling her role as a newly appointed \"tourism ambassador\" for Australia.<ref name=\"Slate2007-01\">{{cite web|url = http://www.slate.com/id/2155910/|title = Say It Ain't So, Dakota!: Paging Jodie Foster|author = Masters, Kim|date = 12 January 2007|work = Newsweek|accessdate = 18 January 2007|url-status = live|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20070118203959/http://www.slate.com/id/2155910|archivedate = 18 January 2007|df = dmy-all}}</ref> Later that month, Irwin appeared on ''[[Larry King Live]]'', where she stated that [[creative writing]] was her favourite subject and maths her least favourite. She also said that she enjoyed being [[Homeschooling|homeschooled]] because she and her teachers were such good friends.{{Citation needed|date=March 2019}}\n\nAlongside [[George Lopez]] and [[Tyler James Williams]], Irwin presented the award for \"Favorite Male Singer\" at the [[2007 Kids' Choice Awards]], which was won by the show's host [[Justin Timberlake]]. With help from [[Glenn Robbins]], Irwin also presented the award for 'Most Outstanding Children's Show' at the [[Logie Awards of 2007]], which was won by ''[[The Upside Down Show]]''.<ref name=\"outstandingshowchildrens\">{{cite web|title=Most Outstanding Children's Show |url=http://tvweek.ninemsn.com.au/section.aspx?sectionid=1923&sectionname=logies&subsectionid=9488&subsectionname=2007nominees |accessdate=26 May 2007 |publisher=ninemsn |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070522213311/http://tvweek.ninemsn.com.au/section.aspx?sectionid=1923&sectionname=logies&subsectionid=9488&subsectionname=2007nominees |archivedate=22 May 2007 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\nIn late November of 2007, Irwin appeared with her mother Terri in the 81st Annual [[Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade]] and performed songs from her album ''Trouble In The Jungle'' with The Crocmen on a jungle animal float.<ref>{{cite web |author='Nigella' |title=2007 Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade \u2013 Celebrity line-up |url=http://www.holidayhacks.com/2007/11/08/2007-macys-thanksgiving-day-parade-celebrity-lineup/ |date=8 November 2007 |access-date=8 October 2015 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110712213506/http://www.holidayhacks.com/2007/11/08/2007-macys-thanksgiving-day-parade-celebrity-lineup/ |archivedate=12 July 2011 |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title = The 81st Annual Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade Kicks Off The Holiday Season With New Iconic Balloons and Floats|url = http://emol.org/virtualmall/macys/news/2007thanksgivingdayparade.html|url-status = live|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20111026190724/http://emol.org/virtualmall/macys/news/2007thanksgivingdayparade.html|archivedate = 26 October 2011|df = dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 May 2008, Irwin won the [[Logie Awards of 2008#Most Popular New Female Talent|Most Popular New Female Talent Logie Award]]. Then on 13 June 2008, at the age of nine, she became the youngest performer ever to win a [[Daytime Emmy Award]] when she won the award for \"[[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Performer in Children's Programming|Outstanding Performer in a Children's Series]]\". The previous record was held by [[Camryn Grimes]], who won the \"Outstanding Younger Actress in a Drama Series\" at age ten for her performance in ''[[The Young and the Restless]]''.\n\nIn addition to singing and dancing Bindi has tried her hand at rapping.\n\nIrwin commits 10% of her wages to [[Wildlife Warriors]], the charity founded by her family in 2002.<ref>{{cite news | first=Megan | last=Lehmann | title=Million dollar baby | date=10 July 2007 | url=http://bulletin.ninemsn.com.au/article.aspx?id=276659 | work=The Bulletin | pages=30\u201335 | accessdate=10 January 2008 | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070911140047/http://bulletin.ninemsn.com.au/article.aspx?id=276659 | archivedate=11 September 2007 | df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Bindi Irwin, 2011.jpg|thumb|Irwin at the [[Logie Awards of 2011]]]] She starred as Kirra in the movie ''[[Free Willy: Escape from Pirate's Cove]]'', released on 23 March 2010.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bindi Irwin stars in Free Willy: South Africa on DVD|work=The Daily Telegraph|last=McWhirter|first=Erin|date=10 March 2009|publisher=News Limited|url=http://www.news.com.au/dailytelegraph/story/0,22049,25166057-5006013,00.html|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090314080410/http://www.news.com.au/dailytelegraph/story/0,22049,25166057-5006013,00.html|archivedate=14 March 2009|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, Irwin hosted a wildlife-themed game show called ''[[Bindi's Bootcamp]]''. Filmed at Australia Zoo, the contestants were put through \"adventure challenges\" to educate and test their wildlife knowledge.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bindi Irwin \"so excited\" about new television show|url=http://www.digitalspy.com/australian-tv/news/a353579/bindi-irwin-so-excited-about-new-television-show.html|first=Rebecca|last=Davies|publisher=digital spy|date=29 November 2011|accessdate=30 November 2011|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120110032252/http://www.digitalspy.com/australian-tv/news/a353579/bindi-irwin-so-excited-about-new-television-show.html|archivedate=10 January 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref> It was produced in association with Sydney-based Sticky Pictures, under commission from ABC, and debuted in July on [[ABC3]].<ref>{{cite news | title=FremantleMedia Enterprises sells Bindi's Bootcamp to Discovery Kids Asia | url=http://if.com.au/2012/08/01/article/FremantleMedia-Enterprises-sells-Bindis-Bootcamp-to-Discovery-Kids-Asia/MYOVSIRIKU.html | author=Candace Wise | date=1 August 2012 | accessdate=15 August 2012 | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120804032742/http://if.com.au/2012/08/01/article/FremantleMedia-Enterprises-sells-Bindis-Bootcamp-to-Discovery-Kids-Asia/MYOVSIRIKU.html | archivedate=4 August 2012 | df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nIrwin starred in the sequel to ''[[Nim's Island]]'' playing the lead character Nim, originally played by [[Abigail Breslin]].<ref>{{cite web | title=Production begins on Nim's Island 2 starring Bindi Irwin | url=http://mumbrella.com.au/production-begins-on-nims-island-2-starring-bindi-irwin-108440 | publisher=mUmBRELLA | date=8 August 2012 | accessdate=15 August 2012 | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120812100205/http://mumbrella.com.au/production-begins-on-nims-island-2-starring-bindi-irwin-108440 | archivedate=12 August 2012 | df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, Irwin appeared as Sunday Clovers on the episode \"Mirror rorriM\" of the [[Canada|Canadian]] television series, ''[[My Babysitter's a Vampire (TV series)|My Babysitter's a Vampire]]''.\n\nIn 2013, Irwin made a brief appearance on the Australian TV series ''[[Big Brother Australia|Big Brother]]'' to surprise housemate Tim, who had mentioned her several times throughout the series, saying \"I want to thank you for being an incredible Wildlife Warrior. I hope when you're out of the house you can come visit me\".\n\nIn March 2014, Irwin appeared on ''[[Good Morning America]]'' with her family, where she announced a partnership with animal theme park company [[SeaWorld]].<ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/nation/why-america-has-turned-on-bindi-irwin-over-seaworld-endorsement/story-e6frg6nf-1226847750778|title = Why America has turned on Bindi Irwin over SeaWorld endorsement|date = 7 March 2015|work = [[The Australian]]|access-date = 19 October 2015|url-status = live|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160801185105/http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/nation/why-america-has-turned-on-bindi-irwin-over-seaworld-endorsement/story-e6frg6nf-1226847750778|archivedate = 1 August 2016|df = dmy-all}}</ref> This decision was strongly criticized by animal rights group [[People for the Ethical Treatment of Animals]], who criticized the Irwin family for supporting a company accused of animal abuse, referencing the documentary ''[[Blackfish (film)|Blackfish]]''.<ref name=peta-bindi-shill>{{cite web|url=http://www.peta.org/media/news-releases/petas-statement-re-bindi-irwin-becomes-seaworlds-latest-shill/|title=PETA's statement, re: Bindi Irwin becomes SeaWorld's latest shill|publisher=PETA|date=6 March 2014|accessdate=8 October 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150924113604/http://www.peta.org/media/news-releases/petas-statement-re-bindi-irwin-becomes-seaworlds-latest-shill/|archivedate=24 September 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2014, Irwin was awarded Young Conservationist of the Year by the [[Australian Geographic Society]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Winners of the 2014 AG Society Awards|url=http://www.australiangeographic.com.au/society/awards/2014/10/australian-geographic-society-awards-2014-winners|publisher=Australian Geographic Society|accessdate=6 October 2015|date=28 October 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151007204540/http://www.australiangeographic.com.au/society/awards/2014/10/australian-geographic-society-awards-2014-winners|archivedate=7 October 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2015, Irwin was announced as a competitor on [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 21)|season 21]] of the American reality television series ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/dancing-stars-season-21-bindi-irwin-revealed-celebrity/story?id=33236211|title=Bindi Irwin to Compete on 'Dancing With the Stars'|work=ABC News|date=24 August 2015|accessdate=24 August 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150825080006/http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/dancing-stars-season-21-bindi-irwin-revealed-celebrity/story?id=33236211|archivedate=25 August 2015|df=dmy-all}}</ref> paired with five-time champion [[Derek Hough]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/691981/dancing-with-the-stars-s-season-21-full-cast-revealed-find-out-the-celebs-and-their-pro-partners/cast-announcement|title=Dancing With the Stars' Season 21 Full Cast Revealed: Find Out the Celebs and Their Pro Partners!|work=[[E!|E! Online]]|date=2 September 2015|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160117164326/http://www.eonline.com/news/691981/dancing-with-the-stars-s-season-21-full-cast-revealed-find-out-the-celebs-and-their-pro-partners/cast-announcement|archivedate=17 January 2016|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Since Irwin was a minor during the competition, she required special permission by California courts to perform.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.etonline.com/news/175453_bindi_irwin_dancing_with_the_stars_contract_rejected_because_judge_wants_proof_her_dad_died|title=Bindi Irwin's 'Dancing With the Stars' Contract Denied Because Judge Wants Proof Her Dad Died|website=Entertainment Tonight|language=en-US|access-date=2019-09-28}}</ref> Irwin and Hough were declared the winners of the season on 24 November 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/2015/11/06/dwts-bindi-irwin-judge/|title=Bindi Irwin: Dancing with the Stars pay held up by judge who needs proof her father died|last=Rice|first=Lynette|date=November 6, 2015|website=Entertainment}}</ref>\n\nOn 1 April 2019, Irwin appeared as a guest judge during week 7 of [[Dancing with the Stars (Australian season 16)|Australian Dancing With The Stars season 16]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://tvtonight.com.au/2019/03/dancing-with-the-stars-apr-1.html |title=Dancing with the Stars: Apr 1 |date=2019-03-29 |website=TV Tonight |access-date=2019-04-01}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nIn July 2019, Irwin became engaged to Chandler Powell, an American professional [[Wakeboarding|wakeboarder]] from Florida. The couple first met at Australia Zoo in November 2013.<ref name=\"cnn250719\"/> On 25 March 2020, they married in a private ceremony at the Australia Zoo.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.abc.net.au/news/2020-03-25/bindi-irwin-marries-chandler-powell-australia-zoo/12089554|title=Bindi Irwin gets married at Australia Zoo, reports say|date=2020-03-25|website=ABC News|language=en-AU|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref> Due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Australia|2020 Coronavirus pandemic]], there were no guests.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/B-KCn5SBLmD/|title=Bindi Irwin on Instagram: \u201cMarch 25th 2020 \u2764\ufe0f We held a small ceremony and I married my best friend. There are no words to describe the amount of love and light in my\u2026\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2020-03-25}}</ref> \n==Music career==\nOn 27 November 2006, Bindi released her debut album ''Bindi Kid Fitness with Steve Irwin and The Crocmen''. A year later on 17 November 2007 she released her first single \"Trouble In The Jungle\". This was the only single to feature Bindi rapping. \"Trouble In The Jungle\" includes a tribute song to Steve called \"My Daddy The Crocodile Hunter\". She then released her second album ''Bindi Kid Fitness 2 Jungle Dance Party'' on 11 October 2008. Bindi originally had a band called Bindi and The Crocmen.<ref>[http://guardianlv.com/2015/07/bindi-irwin-in-the-years-after-the-ghastly-death-of-her-father-video/ Bindi Irwin in the Years After the Ghastly Death of Her Father Video <!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170911072554/http://guardianlv.com/2015/07/bindi-irwin-in-the-years-after-the-ghastly-death-of-her-father-video/ |date=11 September 2017 }}</ref> As of 2009 Bindi has a new band called Bindi and The Jungle Girls.<ref>[http://www.aol.com/article/2016/01/12/bindi-irwin-is-back-at-work-dancing-with-the-jungle-girls/21296126/ Bindi Irwin is back at work dancing with The Jungle Girls <!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170516090503/https://www.aol.com/article/2016/01/12/bindi-irwin-is-back-at-work-dancing-with-the-jungle-girls/21296126/ |date=16 May 2017 }}</ref> Bindi eventually released her third album in 2013 ''Bindi and The Jungle Girls African Dance Party''. Bindi released her fourth album in 2016 ''Bindi and The Jungle Girls Bindi's Island Dance Party''.{{Citation needed|date=February 2019}}\n\n==Discography==\n=== Albums ===\n* ''Bindi Kid Fitness with Steve Irwin and The Crocmen'' (2006)\n* ''Bindi Kid Fitness 2 Jungle Dance Party'' (2008)\n* ''Bindi and The Jungle Girls African Dance Party'' (2013)\n* ''Bindi and The Jungle Girls Bindi's Island Dance Party'' (2016)\n\n=== Singles ===\n* \"Trouble In The Jungle\" (2007)\n\n==Videography==\n* ''Bindi Kid Fitness with Steve Irwin and The Crocmen'' (2006)\n* ''Bindi Kid Fitness 2 Jungle Dance Party'' (2008)\n\n==Filmography==\n\n===Television===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[Wiggly Safari#Video|Wiggly Safari]]''\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Herself\n| Guest Star\n|-\n| 2007\n| rowspan=\"2\" |''[[Bindi the Jungle Girl]]''\n| Host\n|-\n| 2008\n| [[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Performer in Children's Programming]]\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2012\n| ''[[My Babysitter's a Vampire (TV series)|My Babysitter's a Vampire]]''\n| Sunday Clovers\n| Episode: \"Mirror, rorriM\"\n|-\n| ''[[Bindi's Bootcamp]]''\n| Host\n| Gameshow\n|-\n| ''[[Steve Irwin's Wildlife Warriors]]''\n| Herself\n| Co-host\n|-\n|''[[Curious George (TV series)|Curious George]]''\n| Bindi Bungee (Voice)\n| Episode: \"Monkey Down Under/Bright Lights, Little Monkey\" (7.1)\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]''\n| Herself / Contestant\n| [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 21)|Season 21]] winner\n|-\n| 2016\n| ''[[Have You Been Paying Attention?]]''\n|rowspan=\"2\"| Herself\n| Guest Quiz Master\n|-\n| 2018-19\n| ''[[Crikey! It's the Irwins]]''\n| Series regular \n|}\n\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2002\n| ''[[The Crocodile Hunter: Collision Course]]''\n| Herself\n| at the end credits\n|-\n| 2010\n| ''[[Free Willy: Escape from Pirate's Cove]]''\n| Kirra Cooper\n|\n|-\n| 2013\n|  ''[[Return to Nim's Island]]''\n| Nim Rusoe\n|\n|}\n\n===Internet===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2012\n| ''[[Growing Up Wild]]''\n| Herself\n| With her young brother Robert they show their wildest animals at [[Australia Zoo]] on The Pet Collective, a popular animal focused [[YouTube]] channel.\n|}\n\n==''Dancing with the Stars'' performances==\n\nIrwin, who was partnered with [[Derek Hough]], won [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 21)|season 21]] of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)|Dancing with the Stars]]'' (U.S.) on 24 November 2015. Irwin and Hough held the record for the most [[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. TV series)#Number of perfect scores|perfect scores]], with eight. This record was broken by [[Jordan Fisher]] in season 25.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.goldderby.com/article/2017/dancing-with-the-stars-past-winners-poll-jordan-fisher-dwts-news-486259713/|title='Dancing with the Stars' Past Winners: Is Jordan Fisher the best Mirror Ball champion in 'DWTS' history?|last=Montgomery|first=Daniel|date=22 November 2017|website=Gold Derby|access-date=10 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\" style=\"float:left;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#CCCCCC;\" |Week #\n!rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#CCCCCC;\" |Dance / Song\n!colspan=\"3\" style=\"background:#CCCCCC;\" |Judges' scores\n!rowspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#CCCCCC;\" |Result\n|-\n!style=\"background:#CCCCCC;\" width=\"10%\" |Inaba\n!style=\"background:#CCCCCC;\" width=\"10%\" |Hough\n!style=\"background:#CCCCCC;\" width=\"10%\" |Tonioli\n|- style=\"text-align: center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n|1\n|[[Jive (dance)|Jive]] / \"[[Crocodile Rock]]\"\n|8\n|8\n|8\n|No elimination\n|- style=\"text-align: center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n|2\n|[[Ballroom tango|Tango]] / \"[[You Shook Me All Night Long]]\" <br> [[Waltz]] / \"Only a Man\"\n|9<br>7\n|8<br>8\n|8<br>8\n|Safe\n|- style=\"text-align: center; background:#faf6f6;\"\n|3\n|[