{"title_page": "Wehrmacht", "text_new": "{{short description|Unified armed forces of Germany from 1935 to 1945}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox national military\n| name               = ''Wehrmacht''\n| image              = Balkenkreuz.svg\n| alt                = Black cross with white and black outline\n| caption            = Emblem of the ''Wehrmacht'', the ''[[Balkenkreuz]]'', a stylized version of the [[Iron Cross]] seen in varying proportions\n| image2             = War ensign of Germany (1938\u20131945).svg\n| alt2               = Red flag with black Nordic cross, black swastika in the center and black iron cross in the upper left corner\n| caption2           = ''[[Reichskriegsflagge]]'', the war flag and [[naval ensign]] of the ''Wehrmacht'' (1938\u201345 version)\n| motto              = ''[[Gott mit uns]]''{{sfn|Armbr\u00fcster|2005|p=64}}\n| founded            = 16 March 1935\n| current_form       =\n| disbanded          = 20 September 1945{{sfn|M\u00fcller|2016|p=1}}{{efn|The official dissolution of the Wehrmacht began with the [[German Instrument of Surrender]] of 8 May 1945. Reasserted in Proclamation No. 2 of the [[Allied Control Council]] on 20 September 1945, the dissolution was officially declared by ACC Law No. 34 of 20 August 1946.{{sfn|Allied Control Authority|1946a|p=81}}{{sfn|Allied Control Authority|1946b|p=63}}}}\n| branches           = {{plainlist|\n* ''[[German Army (1935\u20131945)|Heer]]'' (army)\n* ''[[Kriegsmarine]]'' (navy)\n* ''[[Luftwaffe]]'' (air force) }}\n| headquarters       = [[Maybach I and II|Maybach II]], [[W\u00fcnsdorf]]\n<!-- Leadership -->\n| commander-in-chief = [[Adolf Hitler]] (first)<br>[[Karl D\u00f6nitz]] (last)\n| commander-in-chief_title = [[#Command structure|Supreme<br>Commander]]\n| chief minister     = [[Adolf Hitler]] (first)<br>[[Werner von Blomberg]] (last)\n| chief minister_title = [[#Command structure|Commander-in-chief]] \n| minister           = Werner von Blomberg\n| minister_title     = [[