mes du IIIe Reich |date=2004 |publisher=Jean-Claude Latt\u00e8s |isbn=978-2709625418 |language=French |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Smelser |first=Ronald |last2=Davies |first2=Edward |authorlink1=Ronald Smelser |title=The Myth of the Eastern Front: the Nazi-Soviet War in American Popular Culture |date=2008 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |location=New York |isbn=978-0-521-83365-3 |ref=harv|title-link=The Myth of the Eastern Front }}\n* {{cite book |last1=Smith |first=Helmut Walser |title=The Oxford Handbook of Modern German History |date=2011 |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=New York |isbn=978-0-19-923739-5 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=IPngdGug27kC&printsec=frontcover |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Stackelberg |first=Roderick |title=The Routledge Companion to Nazi Germany |date=2007 |publisher=Routledge |location=New York |isbn=978-0-41530-861-8 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Stein |first1=George |title=The Waffen-SS: Hitler's Elite Guard at War 1939\u20131945 |publisher=Cerberus Publishing |year=2002 |origyear=1966 |isbn=978-1841451008 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=-KEtPlNQJNgC&pg=PA1#v=onepage&q&f=false |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Stone |first1=David J. |title=Fighting for the Fatherland: The Story of the German Soldier from 1648 to the Present Day |date=2006 |publisher=Potomac Books |location=Herndon, VA |isbn=978-1-59797-069-3 |ref=harv |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/fightingforfathe0000ston }}\n* {{cite book |last1=Strohn |first1=Matthias |title=The German Army and the Defence of the Reich |date=November 2010 |publisher=Cambridge University Press |isbn=9780521191999 |url=https://books.google.com/?id=MTrVCMieFdoC&pg=PA10&lpg=PA10&dq=Reichswehr+changed+to+Wehrmacht#v=onepage&q=Reichswehr%20changed%20to%20Wehrmacht&f=false |accessdate=15 May 2015 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last1=Syrett |first1=David |title=The Defeat of the German U-Boats: The Battle of the Atlantic |date=2010 |publisher=U